Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream surface. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 27. Compare Athenian Agora SS10045, 13913, 14219.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1633)
